reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 26, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good Quality, Works as Advertised
reviews.reviewText: I used to have one of these when I was little. I remembered how neat it was so I got these for my toddler. I wasn’t expecting the best quality, but when they arrived they were perfect. Good sturdy plastic, and the liquids inside disappear at a good rate when tipping the bottle. My daughter loves these for her baby dolls.Great price for two. Highly recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 22, 2023
Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2010
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great little assortment at an awesome price!
reviews.reviewText: I'm very happy with what was in the set we ordered. It looks absolutely nothing like the photo, but I was prepared for that based on other reviews. Bottles, sippy cup, potty, dishes, a velcro diaper, bibs, booties, mittens, assorted bathing items and tiny toys. Everything fits a Fisher Price baby doll that we already have for our 2 1/2 year old. I was happy for the more muted colors, mostly blue and white, and lack of floral in the set that we got as we got this for *gasp* our little boy! He loves to take care of his stuffed animals and baby doll like he sees us take care of his baby brother. He's also potty trained, so the little potty is particularly awesome. This was the perfect set for him and he absolutely loves it. It was one of his favorite Christmas presents. He immediately started feeding his baby doll, putting it on the potty, changing his diaper, putting him to bed, giving him toys to play with, etc. Very educational and encourages his nurturing side.UPDATE: After a month of infrequent use the bag has ripped. The thin floral fabric is tearing away from the edge along the bottom. I really don't care, since the accessories are still in great shape. And I need to get a bag that's a little more macho for my little boy. :) But just giving you all a heads up.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Pretend Play Bottles
reviews.reviewText: A year ago, I decided to enhance my daughter's playtime with her Cabbage Patch dolls by introducing these adorable baby bottles. They were her first set, a perfect fit for a two-year-old's little hands. True enough, they've become a beloved part of her daily play. She cherishes them, frequently seeking out the bottles to ensure her dolls are 'fed'.Over time, the liquid illusion – that charming 'juice' that seems to disappear as the doll drinks – has vanished. While this magical effect was part of the initial appeal, the bottles have otherwise withstood the test of time and toddlerhood. They remain a staple in her pretend kitchen, even without the vanishing act.We've decided to keep them as they still serve their purpose in imaginative play. However, for parents considering longevity in every aspect, investing a bit more in bottles that retain their visual appeal might be worth considering. Despite this, the joy these bottles bring to my daughter is undeniable

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great toddler gift
reviews.reviewText: Love these for little girl gifts! I got these for my grand daughters and they loved them. They are great for learning too, a great empathy teacher. We used them to discuss food, taking care of others, so many things. The bottles have lived through several rough little toddlers too. I worried about them breaking and so far so good. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 23, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The design is easily removed if you prefer plain bottles
reviews.reviewText: I remember having these when I was a kid and was stoked to buy these for my daughter now that she is baby doll obsessed :) Initially I was a tad hesitant because I find the design a little hokey, but ordered them anyways because the price is unbeatable. I was excited to find that the design is actually just a plastic sleeve on the outside of the bottles. I was able to snip the edge with a pair of scissors and then easily unwrap them to reveal plain bottles. These were a big hit with my toddler, and to my surprise, my husband :) He had to inspect them to figure out how they worked. Apparently he didn't have these when he was a kid ;)
I had to buy two one for each child

The baby bottles are super cute and daughter was super happy she loves them one is milk and the other is carrot or orange juice and she calls them magic baby bottles because they refill quickly. I was expecting them to be bigger they are a little small but I guess for dolls it’s perfect size other than that we love it. I would definitely buy again.
Many items to play with! Made a little girlVery happy!

reviews.reviewTitle: My granddaughter plays with her baby all the time. ...
reviews.reviewText: My granddaughter plays with her baby all the time. I even bought the doll care set and never leaves the baby. What her mom does with her she does with the doll. So cute to watch.
